OpenWBEM C++ Provider HOWTO
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Sorry. Didn't have time to provide much documentation on this, so I'm
just going to point you to various components of OpenWBEM for examples.
This will be thoroughly documented in the near future. The examples are listed
below this section.

Once you have a C++ provider built, you can make it available to the CIMOM
by placing the shared library in the directory specified by the
cppprovifc.prov_location option in the CIMOM's configuration file(openwbem.conf)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OW_CppIndicationExportProvider Example:

	./src/provider/OW_CppIndicationExportXMLHTTPProvider.hpp
	./src/provider/OW_CppIndicationExportXMLHTTPProvider.cpp
	
	The OW_CppIndicationExportXMLHTTPProvider class handles the export of
	indications to CIM Listeners using XML over HTTP.

